  <oversight_info>
    <has_dmc>No</has_dmc>
  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This was a non randomised, multi center, italian study performed in burn patients receiving
      an antibiotic (ciprofloxacin) in order to treat an active infection. The aim of the study was
      to validate a pharmacokinetics model useful to verify if a standard dose regimen of
      ciprofloxacin, given to patients with a compromised metabolism, is a correct dose or instead
      is over or under dosed.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
